Description: Two large fragments of a dark brown, loosely woven, wool textile. The weave is plain, and the threads are 's'-twisted. The warp stitch gauge count is 8 per 10mm. The weft is 8 per 10mm.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Kulubnarti, 21-S-2 Float From the vicinity of H-1 and High Street
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
